                  </hi> I am in the service of Mr. Simons, a butcher, of Alpha-road, Chelsea. On 31st March the prisoner came to me for half a pound of steak—he gave me a half-crown—I saw it was bad, and told him so; he produced a good one—Mr. Simons marked the bad one, and gave it to the officer, who took the prisoner.</p>
