                  </hi> I am a trimming-warehouseman. The prisoner came on 1st April for a pair of India-rubber straps—he gave me a half-crown—I gave it to my young man—he gave it back to me bent nearly in two—I went to the shop-door, and asked the prisoner his address—he hesitated, but said, "16, St. Martin's-lane"—I sent for a policeman, and gave him the half-crown.</p>
